    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA248-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu paruvaṅ kaṇṭu āṟṟāḷākiya talaimakaḷait tōḻi maḻai mēlvaittup paruva maṟuttatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante refused [that it was] the season, putting it on the clouds, to HER who was unable to bear it when seeing the season.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA248">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            ciṟuvī mullait tēṅkamaḻ pacuvī</l>
<l>            poṟivari naṉmāṉ pukarmukaṅ kaṭuppat</l>
<l>            taṇputa laṇipeṟa malara vaṇpeyaṟ</l>
<l>            kārvaru paruva meṉṟaṉar maṉṉiṉip</l>
<l>            pēraña ruḷḷa naṭuṅkal kāṇiya </l>
<l>            raṉpiṉ maiyiṟ paṇpila payiṟṟum</l>
<l>            poyyiṭi yatirkural vāycet tālu</l>
<l>            miṉmayiṉ maṭakkaṇam pōla</l>
<l>            niṉaimaruḷ vēṉō vāḻiyar maḻaiyē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>He certainly said</l>
<l rend="indent4">“in the season when the clouds come</l>
<l rend="indent">with generous raining so that the cool bushes flower, to get adorned</l>
<l rend="indent">with green blossoms fragrant with honey on the small-blossomed jasmine,</l>
<l rend="indent2">resembling the spotted faces of the good deer with dots [and] lines”<note place="foot">T.V.G. thinks of an elephant here. But is not one of the spotted antelopes more likely?</note>.</l>
<l rend="indent4">Now,</l>
<l>may you live, rain, will I confuse you [with the monsoon],</l>
<l rend="indent">as [does] the foolish group of pleasing peacocks</l>
<l rend="indent2">that dances, thinking true the shaking voice of the false thunder</l>
<l rend="indent3">that repeats bad [tones], for absence of love [for me],</l>
<l rend="indent4">in order to see [me] shivering inside with big grief?</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
